		</div>
	</header>

	<section class="row-fluid support-content">
		<p class="span6">
			Each Mica watch can be sized to fit any wrist. Extra links are included as well as three precision adjustment settings located on the clasp. Links can be added or removed using mini screwdrivers found in common eyeglass kits.
			<br>
			<br>
			1. To add or remove links, unscrew link pins using 2 flathead screwdrivers on either side (small jewelry screwdrivers) then insert or remove extra links. The screwdrivers needed can be found at most supermarkets or hardware stores for $0.99.
			<br>
			<br>
			2. For a precise fit, remove spring pin from the clasp using the end of a paper clip, tooth pick or thumb tack. Insert spring pin back into any of the three sizing holes.
			<br>
			<br>
			3. If you’re not the do it yourself type, take your watch to any jewelry store to fit it for you.
		</p>
